\subsubsection*{Perceived Penalty Rate}
Mean perceived penalty rate is most sensitive to the following model options: targeted auditing, tax refund effect, and mild tendency to evade full income. It is also sensitive to network effect but not very significant compared to others. Bomb crater effect, gambler's fallacy  and media effect have negative scores with respect to the sensitivity of mean perceived penalty rate.

