\subsubsection*{Compliance and Non-Compliance}
In this model, we say an agent is compliant if the agent reports 95 percent or more of the agent's income. Any agent reporting less than 95 percent of the income is considered non compliant. Also, agents reporting less than 5 percent of their income are categorized in the zero-reporting category. As shown in the figure below proportion of compliance in the model is highly sensitive to tax refund effect, and mild tendency to fully evade income. Third, most sensitive model option is the network effect. Targeted auditing, media effect, gambler's fallacy, bomb crater effect produce very little variation in proportion of compliance.

